                <h2>Project Impact</h2>
                <p>After the implementation of VIJANA WA AMANI project, we expect significant qualitative impacts in youth and community, including enhanced self confidence and self esteem, improved leadership skills, improved respect for the positive role of youth within communities, reduced caste and ethnic barriers to interaction and collaboration between youth and enhanced dispute resolution capacities.  Over the life of the project, a significant decrease in quantitative indicators will be observed. In addition to other efforts made by International humanitarian organizations and Peacebuilding programs, VIJANA WA AMANI also make a significant contribution by getting youth (ex-combatants) reintegrated in their communities.</p>

                <p>VIJANA WA AMANI project will benefit socially and economically for the communities resilience, specifically for disadvantaged group; returnee refugees, displaced, women victims of rape and education of children ex-combatants, and to build a peaceful spaces for youth, children and women.</p>
